-- Danish August forex reserves rise to 441.6 bln DKK
-- 
-- Tue Sep 02, 2014 10:08AM EDT
-- None



COPENHAGEN, Sept 2 (Reuters) - Denmark's foreign exchange reserves, a monetary policy tool, rose to 441.6 billion Danish crowns ($77.8 billion) in August from 440.9 in July, the central bank said on Tuesday.

